<task id="021" project="sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2">
  <metadata>
    <title>P2.W2 — Fix RB-T044-04: CitationExtractor.NormalizePatent EP/WO branches double-prefix country code</title>
    <phase>Phase 2</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>1-2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>013,020</dependencies>
    <blocks>029</blocks>
    <tags>phase-2, bff-api, real-bug-ledger, medium-severity, production-fix, ai</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Production code change in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety/Citations/CitationExtractor.cs`; Step 9.5 code-review + adr-check mandatory per CLAUDE.md §8 FULL rigor decision tree</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>P2-W2</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>File-overlap with task 020 (both touch `CitationExtractor.cs`). Must run sequentially AFTER 020 commits to avoid merge race. Parallel-safe with any non-CitationExtractor peer in the same sub-wave.</parallel-reason>
    <production-fix-per-ledger>true</production-fix-per-ledger>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Close real-bug-ledger entry **RB-T044-04** by fixing the production bug in `CitationExtractor.NormalizePatent`. The EP and WO branches of the normalizer PREPEND the literal `"EP"` / `"WO"` even though the regex capture groups ALREADY include the country-code prefix in the captured value. Result: `EP3456789` → `EPEP3456789`. The US branch is correct (its `(?<us>[\d,]{5,15})` captures digits-only).

    The ledger's recommended fix (lines 378-388): **drop the literal prefix** in the EP and WO branches; rely on the captured-value already containing the country code:

    ```csharp
    if (m.Groups["ep"].Success)
        return Regex.Replace(m.Groups["ep"].Value, @"[^\dA-Za-z]", "");

    if (m.Groups["wo"].Success)
        return Regex.Replace(m.Groups["wo"].Value, @"[^\dA-Za-z/]", "");
    ```

    Per D-02, this single production fix closes ONE ledger entry. Per NFR-04, the commit message MUST cite `RB-T044-04` + resolution mode `repaired`. Per NFR-02, line replacement <50%.
  </prompt>

  <role>Backend AI agent fixing production code in `Services/Ai/Safety/Citations/` to close a MEDIUM-severity real-bug ledger entry.</role>

  <goal>
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety/Citations/CitationExtractor.cs` `NormalizePatent` EP and WO branches no longer double-prefix the country code. The 2 InlineData cases in `ExtractCitations_Patent_NonUS_MatchedAndNormalized` (EP, WO) flip Skip → Pass. US Patent Theory cases remain green. RB-T044-04 transitions to `repaired`.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
