  <context>
    <background>
      Same file as task 020 (`CitationExtractor.cs`). Task 020 fixes the US/Case Law branch (`NormalizeCaseLaw`); this task fixes the non-US/Patent branches (`NormalizePatent` EP + WO). The two fixes are independent within the file (different methods); however running them in parallel would create a `git` merge race on the same file. This task runs in Wave 2 AFTER task 020 lands.

      Per the ledger: the EP and WO capture groups in the patent regex include the country-code prefix in the matched value. The current normalizer code prepends the literal `"EP"` (or `"WO"`) again, producing the documented `EPEP3456789` corruption pattern. The US branch is correct because its capture group is digits-only and the normalizer correctly prepends `"US"`.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="013" status="required">Phase 1 exit triple-run validated</dependency>
      <dependency task="020" status="required">RB-T044-02 fix lands first (same file)</dependency>
    </dependencies>
