  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety/Citations/CitationExtractor.cs</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Safety/CitationExtractorTests.cs</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load RB-T044-04 ledger entry (lines 360-393 in real-bug-ledger.md). Confirm Status not yet `repaired`.</step>
    <step order="2">Verify task 020 (RB-T044-02) is committed (Status: `repaired`). If not, abort and wait for sub-wave gating.</step>
    <step order="3">Read `CitationExtractor.cs` `NormalizePatent` method (line 180 per ledger). Identify the EP and WO branches; confirm the double-prefix pattern by hand-tracing the regex.</step>
    <step order="4">Apply the production fix per the ledger §378-388: replace the EP branch return with `Regex.Replace(m.Groups["ep"].Value, @"[^\dA-Za-z]", "")` (no literal prefix); apply equivalent fix to the WO branch using `@"[^\dA-Za-z/]"`. Verify the US branch is unchanged.</step>
    <step order="5">Remove `Skip = "..."` + per-Theory `[Trait("status","real-bug-pending-fix")]` on `ExtractCitations_Patent_NonUS_MatchedAndNormalized` (2 InlineData: EP, WO).</step>
    <step order="6">Build: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`. Verify 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="7">Run targeted tests: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~CitationExtractorTests"`. Confirm EP + WO InlineData pass + US Patent + CaseLaw + Statute + Regulation cases still pass.</step>
    <step order="8">Step 9.5 quality gates: `code-review` + `adr-check`. Verify <50% line replacement; no DI changes (ADR-010); AI/Safety stays in-process (ADR-013).</step>
    <step order="9">Update RB-T044-04 ledger entry: Status → `repaired`; fix-commit SHA + date.</step>
    <step order="10">Commit: `fix(ai/safety): remove double country-code prefix in CitationExtractor.NormalizePatent EP/WO (RB-T044-04; repaired)`. Update `current-task.md`.</step>
  </steps>

